caption: Great place to share drinks and a quick bite with friends. Even better that they're dog friendly!  Good beer options but my go to drink is always the cider on tap.  Ordered the Salad #1, Brussel Sprouts, Mac & Cheese Bites, Pulled Pork Sandwich.  Rave reviews from all on the Brussel Sprouts and fries. Mac & Cheese Bites were also yummy. I would not at all recommend the salad, quite sad and small, certainly not worth the price.

(Translated by Google) It is simply one of my favorite restaurants. Excellent all the dishes we ordered, each one very happy with what they ordered and the truffle fries are worth the extra price. Hoping that by the time we return they already have the new dishes on the menu. Very friendly service and very calm atmosphere.  (Original) Simplemente es uno de mis restaurantes favoritos. Excelentes todos los platillos que pedimos, cada uno muy contento con lo que pidió y las patatas fritas con trufa valen el precio extra. Esperando que para cuando regresemos ya tengan los nuevos platillos en el menú. El servicio muy amable y el ambiente muy tranquilo.
Great hangout spot and is right on the corner where I live!! Staff is awesome, great drinks and ambience
Nice place, kind service and tasty food, especially the truffle fries and burger!

Everything about this place was great! Great food (their salmon sandwich alone was reason enough to want to come back), great drinks (especially their fun dip margarita), and great service! This place is definitely worth a second and third visit, I will be adding it to my list of must visit again.
The wait for food is unbearably long.
The staff is engaging and experienced. Their selection of food and drinks go well together in this location.

The Best Spacious Outdoor Seating in the Heights & pet friendly❗️Chief Dre is the Best, the thai chilli wings are fire so is so is the Stinky Burger! E-Money🤑 makes Bomb cocktails and my fav Beer on Draft is the Centennial IPA 💫🤩

Do you know that feeling you get after something unexpectedly good happened to you?  Like making a left turn that felt unsure but ending up right where you wanted to be all along.  Thats the feeling that washed over me after leaving my first visit at Barrell 79.  Upon my entrance I was greeted by the Messiah of the bar.  This guy looks like a swimsuit model Jesus that Gucci would cast to headline their most important runway show of all time.  I later discovered he was one of the proprietors of the establishment.  He must clean up that's all Im saying.  Anyway, apparently he's from the midwest and his hospitality truly showed.  He helped guide me to the drinks that would suit my tastes by asking me qualifying questions which made quite an impression on me from the start.  The staff continued to be attentive as they ran through their food specials.  I ended up going with a sandwich called Moms Parmesan Burger which has a parmesan crusted bun which is insanely delicious along with the healthy meat patty and a flavorful aoli sauce.  Im not sure which one of their moms they named this after but she's going straight to heaven Im sure of it.  So, after I finnish by murger I started inquiry on their specialty cocktails since my 7th IPA was looking a lillow.  Earlier I had mentioned a scratchy throat casually to the surferr and he helpfully sushested I try this phenomenal drink called the Hot 2 Trot whit chas whisky, fresh lemon, cloves and honey and is made with real hot water.  Talk about a nawesome drink.  So I stuck roundan had 4 more those and was feeling prilly grate.  I made frans with some the other patrons at the bar an they said effry Friday they come frappy hour.  I told so corkers and frans bout the place an we're definitely coming back here freshure.  Ssplace is now my new fafrit place fall time fshure.  In all seriousness this is a great place to enjoy a tasty, fresh and mindfully made meal at a reasonable price and then get treated like gold while you enjoy a few drinks.  The atmosphere is very welcoming and thoughtfully designed.  Its cozy and intimate yet spacious and welcoming.  This is going to be my regular spot.  They have TVs everywhere and a great sound system too.  What an awesome addition to the neighborhood.  I give it all the STARS.  Check it out.

Only place that we’ve been to that I can honestly say didn’t have any negatives! The staff are extremely friendly and accommodating, the food tasted great, and the drinks were awesome! Definitely will be heading back and becoming a regular!
Nicholas is a pretty cool dude
Love this place 😃👌👌
Service, atmosphere, and food are great!

The food was delicious (definitely recommend the guac!) And the staff was friendly and welcoming. And I appreciated that they labeled all of the vegan options on their menu.
Great place to have drink and food.
Very cozy place excellent service and delicious food, coming back for sure and the owner was very friendly
Disappointing.  Really dull, unimaginative, unhealthy menu.  Server didn't know what it meant to serve a drink neat.  Drinks were overpriced.  Restaurant was unpleasantly loud.
Excellent place... Hidden away in the middle of nowhere!

Ate here last weekend.  Loved this place.  Had great food and great service.  Also in a nice safe neighborhood.  Highly recommend.  I would skip the fun dip margarita tho. It was extremely sweet.  Everything else, food, drinks and service was great.  Hope this place is successful - they deserve to be!
Great food and great drinks
Had lunch after 11am, only had breakfast menu available. No coffee available at that time?! Pancakes were good. Friends ate burgers there a couple of days earlier and they were pleased.

I ordered the wings to go: delicious!  My first experience we ate in. It wasn’t the best. HARD NO on the barrel roll. It was too hot to eat as served. When it cools, the coating is too hard to consume. We also had burgers, fries, the fun dip margarita, and another appetizer I can’t recall. All of it was really good! We took the remainder to go, when we got home the server threw away but the burger.  I was really annoyed by that and the slow service but the wings looked good coming from kitchen. I went back to try them. The service was speedy, the wings were amazing and the owner, Nick, made it a delightful visit. I’ll be back. A few times a month

Met a few friends for drinks.  The place was empty.  $1 off draft beer and no food specials.  The bartender appeared to me new.  When a friend asked for a screwdriver,  he did not know what that was.  Very Interesting!  The place is very nicely decorated.  Hope it does well in this neighborhood.
This a great cozy spot to come by, grab some drinks and food with friends. The staff is friendly and the food and drink is just right for after work.

The first thing I'd like to give them credit for is their appearance. I drove by, it caught my eye, and I decided to park the car and give them a try. The staff instantly greeted me as I entered. I ordered the Stinky Burger well-done. They prepared the burger just how I like it. My only suggestion would be for Barrel 79 to add a little more seasoning and always remember to provide customers with napkins & silverware. I don't think I'd stop in for food again, but if I did, it would probably be to sample their drinks. It seemed like everyone was enjoying their drinks.
The grilled chicken and pulled pork sandwiches were very tasty. + super friendly staffs. It is a gem of the neighborhood.
Great food +drinks
Cool vibes, food and drinks. Had a good night with friends - the deep fried avocado wedges were on point. This spot is a great addition to the heights.

In addition to slow service, the beer pours are small (many 12 oz), the selection is minimal, and the prices are high.  Lagunitas IPA is not a craft beer.  Appetizers are okay but a small handful of chips for $9 is too much. Interior is nice and the vibe is chill, could be a great place but they charge way too much for what they offer.
Nice quiet place. Guac is good. Drinks are good. It don't drink the tap water. Its warm and disgusting
Great food and exceptional service, nice staff and amazing atmosphere is the best place for hangout with friends 🤙

Delicious drinks and amazing service from Ariel!

The staff is super friendly and the drinks are great! Wine on tap is pretty decent at really good pricing. Fried Mac and cheese were good and the wings were meaty. Excited to try the burgers next time!
food and drinks are incredible

OBSESSED!! Holy wings... holy burger (plus tots)- I’m still stuffed! Gone a few times since they opened and the food is 👍🏽, staff is great & vibes are cool. Totally dig the spot & I love all the little trinkets there too!

In short, an exceptional and highly recommended place.  (Original) Barrel 79 es un bar con un excelente ambiente muy acogedor. El personal provee un servicio impecable, haciendo sentir a gusto al cliente. En definitivo un lugar excepcional y muy recomendado.
Good food, cold bear, pleasant staff....Mad props to Rory, Ariel, the twins and Aris behind the bar! The staff on the floor is also very attentive.

Barrel 79 is a fantastic place to go for their happy hour or at night to hang out with friends! I live in Harlem, but make the trip up to Washington heights for their amazing food and great drinks! I definitely suggest trying a front porch!
LOVED the fried pickles. Burgers great too. Staff awesome, first timer, I’ll be back! Welcome to The Heights!

Went into this new bar in my neighborhood on Friday and it was the right choice!! Employees are friendly service is great. The food is simple but very good, not overly priced like most bars in the city. The environment is welcoming and the music was GREAT!! 90's and early 2000 hip-hop loud enough to hear and also be able to carry a conversation without screaming. The custom made wood bartop is absolutely beautiful. Found my new happy place around the block for happy hour.. 😊

Great place and environment! Good food and staff! The drinks are delicious and creative, especially the fun dipped tequila!  Only had 3 issues: Ordered mozzarella wedges which are 6 for $8 and only received 3 and was charged full price. Even though it was happy hour still got fully charged for my drinks and even overcharged one dollar for one drink. And one of the FOH staff kept going to the back to look at her phone instead of paying attention to customers. Had to get up to get her attention.  Since the place is only two days all these are all fixable things, hope it helps to keep the place great! Highly recommend!

The food is simple, straightforward and delicious, and the drinks are strong. Creative signature cocktails, great selection of local beer and wine on tap. Really awesome, friendly staff. The neighborhood desperately needed a place like Barrel! So happy they are finally open.

I stopped by this cool looking new place in my neighborhood tonight. It's got garage door windows that were open bar seating some custom wood bars and the best damn Burger I've had in a long long time.
